
<h2>
    Background Colors
</h2>
<p>
    Possible color values can be defined by:
    <ul>
        <li>
            name (like <code>red</code>)
        </li>
        <li>
            hex <code>#FF0000</code>
        </li>
        <li>
            rgb value <code>rgb(255,0,0)</code>
        </li>
    </ul><p>
        Use one of these values with background-color to change the 
    background color of an element.     
    </p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    background-color: red; /* <-- using name */
}

p {
    background-color: rgb(255, 0, 0); /* <-- using rgb */
}

p {
    background-color: #ff0000; /* <-- using hex value */
}
</code></pre>
</p>

<h3>
    transparent background  colors
</h3>
<p>
    Along with changing <code>background-color</code>, <code>opacity</code> can also be 
    modified to change the background transparency. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    background-color: #ff0000; 
    opacity: 60%; /* <-- change transparency */
    }
</code></pre>

<p style="
    background-color: #ff0000; 
    opacity: 60%;
    margin-left: 3%;
    height: 200px;
    ">
    opacity: 60%
</p>

<h3>
    rgba and transparency
</h3>
<p>
    Another way to make backgrounds transparent is to use 
    <code>rgba()</code>, with the last value being a decimal 
    between 0 and 1. Lower values are more transparent.
</p>


<pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    background-color: rgba(255,0,0,.6); 
    }
</code></pre>
<p style="
    background-color: rgba(255,0,0,.6); 
    margin-left: 3%;
    height: 200px;
    ">
    opacity: 60%
</p>
