<h2>
    Background-image
</h2>
<p>
    The background-image property names an image to use as a background instead of a color.
</p>
<p>
    Something to note: the image will repeat itself until the space is full by default. To give the path of 
    the background-image, use <code>url(**path)</code>. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">body {
    background-image: url("python-logo-only.svg");
    }
</code></pre>
